Global gold demand grew to 10533 tonnes in 1Q19 up 7 yy This compares with a relatively weak 1Q18 when demand sank to a 3 year low of just 9842t Central bank buying continued apace global gold reserves grew by 1455t Goldbacked ETFs also saw growth quarterly inflows into those products grew by 49 to 403t Total bar and coin investment weakened a fraction to 2578t 1 due to a fall in demand for gold bars official gold coin buying grew 12 to 561t Jewellery demand was stronger yy at 5303t chiefly due to improvement in Indias market Technology dipped to 2year low of 793t hit by slower economic growth The supply of gold in Q1 was virtually unchanged just 3t lower yy at 1150t GLD GDX
